Inspector General of Police Joseph Boinnet has warned Kenyans to be on the lookout for possible terror threats during the festive season. In a statement on Tuesday, he urged Kenyans to report suspicious persons or activities to police. &ldquo;The terror threat remains a reality. We call upon the public to remain vigilant, particularly in places with high concentration of people. These include beaches, restaurants, and clubs, as well as places of worship,&rdquo; the statement reads. Boinnet said they are joining forces to ensure road safety. The teams include the Police Service, the National Transport and Safety Authority and the Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission. Coast regional coordinator Nelson Marwa yesterday assured tourists travelling to the Coast of increased security. &ldquo;We assure them of their safety during and after the festive season,&rdquo; the commissioner told the Star.